<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 94 / Age discrimination unfair
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Age discrimination by employers and recruiters should be against the law, a
pressure group said yesterday.
Mr Richard Worsley, director of the Carnegie Third Age Programme, which
deals with issues concerning older people, said there was a need for one law
to tackle discrimination in employment.
Mr Worsley told the Harrogate conference that unjustified age discrimination
was preventing the 14m people in Britain aged between 50 and 74 from making
an important contribution to the economy.
Government consultation on proposals for legislation to end discrimination
against disabled people, he said, held out the possibility that age
discrimination would be neglected and unregulated, outside the equal
opportunities agenda.
