FT  28 OCT 94 / World Trade News: Gatt waiver sought for Lome
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Union and the African, Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) states have
jointly applied for a waiver from the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade
(Gatt) fair trade rules for the Lome Convention, a European Commission
official said yesterday. The official said the Commission was satisfied that
the preferential trading arrangements of the Lome Convention, intended to
aid 46 developing countries, were compatible with Gatt.
He said the waiver request was a precaution in view of criticism of Lome by
a Gatt panel which attacked the EU's banana import regime as contrary to
world trade rules. The Gatt Council is due to consider the waiver request on
November 10.
