<TEXT>
Antonio Canova's The Three Graces will stay in the UK after the Court of
Appeal rejected a challenge by the Getty Museum of California, which paid
Pounds 7.6m for the statue, against a government decision to delay the
granting of an export licence. The move allowed UK galleries time to raise a
similar amount to keep the work in Britain.
