<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 94 / International Company News: Browning-Ferris advances 41% on
acquisitions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Acquisitions and a strong improvement in recycling prices helped
Browning-Ferris Industries, the US waste company, to report a 41 per cent
jump in annual net income to Dollars 278.7m, writes Peggy Hollinger.
Mr William Ruckelshaus, chairman and chief executive, said he was pleased
with the results, which included a 55 per cent increase in fourth-quarter
net income to Dollars 82.3m. Sales for the quarter were 34 per cent ahead at
Dollars 1.24bn, and 24 per cent up for the full year at Dollars 4.3bn.
'A successful acquisition programme, improved commodity prices and an
expanding economy contributed to these results,' he said.
BFI, which is pursuing a hostile Pounds 364m bid for Attwoods of the UK,
bought 25 companies during the final quarter, adding about Dollars 100m in
extra sales.
Net income per share rose to Dollars 1.49 from Dollars 1.15.
</TEXT>
