<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 94 / International Company News: Shell Oil up by one-third at
Dollars 323m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Shell Oil, the US arm of the Royal Dutch/Shell group, said after-tax profits
before one-off factors rose by one-third, to Dollars 323m, in the three
months to the end of September, writes Richard Waters in New York.
Higher-than-expected production from the Augur field in the Gulf of Mexico
and lower exploration costs led to a Dollars 50m rise in operating income
from exploration and production, to Dollars 151m, before one-off charges.
In spite of the lower profit margins in the refinery business that have
afflicted the rest of the industry, the company reported a Dollars 9m
increase to Dollars 119m in underlying income from oil products, due to
volume increases. Operating income from chemicals also advanced, with income
climbing Dollars 33m to Dollars 100m.
Including all one-off factors, net income rose to Dollars 313m from Dollars
187m a year ago.
