<HEADLINE>
FT  28 OCT 94 / Hughes attacks damages award
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE KEHOE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAN FRANCISCO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hughes Aircraft, a General Motors subsidiary, described as 'irrational,
irresponsible and outrageous' the Dollars 89.5m damages award against the
company handed down this week by a Los Angeles jury. In the case, which
involves two former Hughes employees, one white and one black, the company
was found to have violated fair employment laws. Hughes intends to appeal
and legal experts said the award would almost certainly be reduced
substantially.
The award comes amid a rash of discrimination and harassment suits. In
another high profile case the US Labor Department, which is supposed to be a
watchdog against workplace discrimination, agreed to pay an estimated
Dollars 4.9m to settle a suit that accused the agency of discrimination
against its own black employees. Businesses complain that despite efforts to
eliminate bias in the workplace, increasingly restrictive laws make it very
hard to comply.
</TEXT>
