<HEADLINE>
FT  27 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Canada
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gains in Toronto for oil and metal stocks helped break the TSE 300 composite
index's four-day losing streak with a moderate advance.
According to preliminary data, the TSE 300 composite index gained 17.18
points, or 0.40%, to 4,259.95 on volume of 54.845m shares valued at CDollars
708m.
Ten of the 14 sub-indexes were up, led by oil and gas, metal and
transportation stocks. Gold and real estate stocks posted the biggest
declines.
