<HEADLINE>
FT  27 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Exploration/El Oro
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Exploration Company, which despite its title operates as an investment
dealing company, lifted first half profits to Pounds 1.04m pre-tax, against
Pounds 827,000.
The outcome, for the six months to June 30, reflected sharply higher profits
from investments. This offset lower returns from associates, dividends,
rents and interest.
Earnings per stock unit improved from 4.89p to 6.09p.
The associated El Oro Mining &amp; Exploration - also an investment dealing
company - reported pre-tax profits of Pounds 766,000 (Pounds 751,000) for
the same period, giving earnings of 12.06p (11.73p) per share.
