<HEADLINE>
FT  27 OCT 94 / Research plan cut
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government has withdrawn its plans to ask all students aiming for a
three-year science doctorate to take a one-year masters qualification in
research first. The aim was to filter out students who would not pass their
doctorate and thus cut wastage of government research council funds.
