<HEADLINE>
FT  27 OCT 94 / Council wins in MetroCentre case
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gateshead Borough Council has won a test case ruling that a unit at the
MetroCentre retail development requires planning permission for a change
from retail to restaurant use.
But in a second decision, also announced yesterday, the Department of the
Environment found in favour of the Church Commissioners, the MetroCentre's
owners, with a ruling that the erection of a sign and glazed shop front at
another MetroCentre unit did not require permission.
